N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 2109.6 - Disclosure of information by the administrator

State Regulations

The administrator shall not publish or disclose any
information obtained under the act or this Subchapter that the administrator
deems confidential or with reference to which a request for confidential
treatment is made by the person furnishing such information, unless the
administrator determines that the withholding thereof is contrary to the public
interest. Notes
